1
00:00:03,296 --> 00:00:05,507
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,632 --> 00:00:08,259
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,384 --> 00:00:13,389
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,515 --> 00:00:18,561
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:26,945 --> 00:00:31,282
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,407 --> 00:00:35,411
<i>I'm going to change the dream</i>

7
00:00:35,537 --> 00:00:39,749
<i>Into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,585 --> 00:00:48,466
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,591 --> 00:00:51,636
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,595 --> 00:00:54,847
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,973 --> 00:00:57,642
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:02,564
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,730 --> 00:01:07,944
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:08,069 --> 00:01:11,489
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,614 --> 00:01:17,328
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:26,713 --> 00:01:27,672
What?!

17
00:01:28,464 --> 00:01:32,343
There were another
<i>23</i> heart attack victims yesterday?!

18
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:35,763
<i>As soon as we began to suspect
that Kira was a student,</i>

19
00:01:35,888 --> 00:01:38,641
<i>the timing of the killings changed as
if to contradict our theory.</i>

20
00:01:38,766 --> 00:01:41,728
Does that mean that Kira knows
what the police know?

21
00:01:42,270 --> 00:01:44,772
When L discovers that information
from the investigation was leaked,

22
00:01:44,897 --> 00:01:48,943
he's bound to search for leads on me
within the police force.

23
00:01:49,193 --> 00:01:52,530
Someone's been following you
all this time.

24
00:01:55,408 --> 00:01:56,826
That's a problem...

25
00:01:56,951 --> 00:01:59,120
I'll get rid of him soon, Ryuk.

26
00:02:00,371 --> 00:02:02,081
A Shinigami's eyes...

27
00:02:02,206 --> 00:02:05,835
...can see a human's name
and lifespan above their heads.

28
00:02:05,835 --> 00:02:06,711
LIGHT YAGAMI

29
00:02:06,711 --> 00:02:11,090
Shinigami can also turn the eyes
of whoever picked up their Death Note

30
00:02:11,215 --> 00:02:13,635
into Shinigami eyes.

31
00:02:14,469 --> 00:02:16,846
The price for a Shinigami's eyes...

32
00:02:17,472 --> 00:02:20,975
is half of that human's remaining lifetime.

33
00:02:22,644 --> 00:02:23,770
So...

34
00:02:23,895 --> 00:02:25,938
Light, what'll it be?

35
00:02:26,105 --> 00:02:28,983
PURSUIT

36
00:02:29,817 --> 00:02:32,236
I haven't seen Ryuk around lately...

37
00:02:32,612 --> 00:02:35,782
Did he really lose his Death Note
in the Human World?

38
00:02:35,907 --> 00:02:38,660
The Death Note was probably picked up
by a human before he got to it.

39
00:02:38,785 --> 00:02:39,744
Couldn't be...

40
00:02:39,869 --> 00:02:42,330
If that happened to him, he'd have to
follow that person around

41
00:02:42,455 --> 00:02:45,333
until that person dies
or the Death Note is destroyed.

42
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:49,337
Yeah... I can't picture Ryuk
doing something so tedious.

43
00:02:49,504 --> 00:02:53,383
But I've heard that he was
carrying two Death Notes.

44
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:56,469
Seriously?
Why would he need two?

45
00:02:56,594 --> 00:02:58,888
I have no idea what drives him to
do what he does.

46
00:03:00,807 --> 00:03:02,975
In order for me to gain
the eyes of a Shinigami...

47
00:03:03,351 --> 00:03:06,062
I have to offer half of my life.

48
00:03:06,813 --> 00:03:07,980
Is that right?

49
00:03:08,564 --> 00:03:09,524
Yeah.

50
00:03:09,565 --> 00:03:10,775
So what'll it be?

51
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,360
Do you wanna make
a deal?

52
00:03:13,528 --> 00:03:14,529
Ryuk.

53
00:03:16,823 --> 00:03:19,701
This deal...
is out of the question.

54
00:03:32,755 --> 00:03:34,173
Listen.

55
00:03:34,632 --> 00:03:38,010
I want to create an ideal,
new world free from criminals.

56
00:03:38,177 --> 00:03:41,472
I also intend to reign as
the god in that world for a long time.

57
00:03:42,473 --> 00:03:44,934
I would consider it if
it lengthened my life,

58
00:03:45,059 --> 00:03:46,936
but it's not worth talking
about if it's going to shorten it.

59
00:03:47,937 --> 00:03:49,856
You, of all people,
should know that.

60
00:03:50,481 --> 00:03:54,777
Yeah, I just felt I should tell
you a deal like this exists.

61
00:03:55,361 --> 00:03:59,532
I don't want you to complain that
I didn't tell you about this earlier.

62
00:04:00,533 --> 00:04:02,910
If you didn't tell me
about this earlier?

63
00:04:03,119 --> 00:04:05,246
Don't you think
you're too late already?

64
00:04:05,371 --> 00:04:08,207
You should have told me this
when we first met

65
00:04:08,332 --> 00:04:12,128
or included this when you were writing
instructions in the Death Note...

66
00:04:12,545 --> 00:04:13,963
Yeah. I guess you're right.

67
00:04:14,714 --> 00:04:16,299
<i>Even though I'm a Shinigami,</i>

68
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:17,633
<i>he's never been afraid of me or</i>

69
00:04:17,675 --> 00:04:20,511
<i>tried to kiss my butt when
it comes to things like this.</i>

70
00:04:20,553 --> 00:04:22,388
<i>He just gives me a hard time...</i>

71
00:04:27,852 --> 00:04:28,853
Well?

72
00:04:29,604 --> 00:04:32,482
You sure there isn't anything else you
want to tell me ahead of time?

73
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:34,275
Ryuk, the Shinigami?

74
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:36,611
Nope, there's nothing else...

75
00:04:37,236 --> 00:04:38,237
<i>Probably...</i>

76
00:04:38,571 --> 00:04:40,031
I see.
How disappointing.

77
00:04:40,698 --> 00:04:41,741
"Disappointing"?

78
00:04:41,991 --> 00:04:43,826
I may have seriously
considered the deal

79
00:04:43,951 --> 00:04:46,120
if you offered me wings
rather than eyes.

80
00:04:46,746 --> 00:04:50,291
Wouldn't flying around in the sky
with wings be godlike?

81
00:04:51,334 --> 00:04:54,629
It's a dream that man
has had since ancient times.

82
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:58,299
You'd stand out if you sprouted
wings and started flying around.

83
00:04:58,883 --> 00:05:01,010
I'd bet you'd get arrested
by the police just for that.

84
00:05:01,719 --> 00:05:02,887
Ryuk, that was a joke.

85
00:05:04,764 --> 00:05:08,726
However, if I continue to
cut deals for eyes and wings...

86
00:05:08,935 --> 00:05:11,395
I'm going to end up becoming
a real Shinigami.

87
00:05:12,396 --> 00:05:14,482
That could be amusing,
don't you think?

88
00:05:15,316 --> 00:05:16,734
Don't worry.

89
00:05:16,859 --> 00:05:20,029
Even without all that,
you're already...

90
00:05:20,613 --> 00:05:22,448
a fine Shinigami!

91
00:05:23,741 --> 00:05:26,702
The Shinigami Realm is
rotten these days.

92
00:05:27,203 --> 00:05:31,624
They all live vacant lives
and only take human lives...

93
00:05:31,749 --> 00:05:34,335
just because they don't want to die.

94
00:05:34,752 --> 00:05:36,921
No one even knows...

95
00:05:37,380 --> 00:05:39,465
why we exist.

96
00:05:39,841 --> 00:05:43,427
I doubt there's any reason
at all for our existence.

97
00:05:45,304 --> 00:05:50,142
You're much more of
a Shinigami than they are.

98
00:05:50,434 --> 00:05:55,565
Well, from what you're saying, it sounds
like I'm doing a lot more work.

99
00:05:56,315 --> 00:05:58,776
But don't lump me together
with the Shinigami.

100
00:05:59,235 --> 00:06:03,614
I am using this Death Note
as a human for humans.

101
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:07,952
But, I wouldn't say that
the Shinigami Realm

102
00:06:08,077 --> 00:06:10,580
is meaningless to humans either.

103
00:06:11,455 --> 00:06:12,665
What do you mean?

104
00:06:13,374 --> 00:06:14,458
Well, think about it.

105
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,295
Whenever a Shinigami like you
comes to the Human World

106
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:20,214
once every hundred, no,
every thousand years,

107
00:06:20,339 --> 00:06:22,383
the Human World
changes greatly.

108
00:06:23,175 --> 00:06:26,304
The Shinigami Realm's existence
is fearfully meaningful.

109
00:06:26,846 --> 00:06:28,097
I-Is that so?

110
00:06:28,723 --> 00:06:31,684
You just told me that
the Shinigami Realm is rotten.

111
00:06:32,143 --> 00:06:33,352
When you return there,
from this world,

112
00:06:33,477 --> 00:06:36,522
how about using what you've
learned here to try to change it?

113
00:06:38,024 --> 00:06:43,696
Light. . .you just may be
quite the positive thinker.

114
00:06:45,531 --> 00:06:46,741
Of course, I am.

115
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:49,869
If I wasn't, I wouldn't be
trying to use

116
00:06:49,994 --> 00:06:52,705
the Death Note to try and
make the world a better place.

117
00:06:56,334 --> 00:06:57,376
That's it!

118
00:06:58,669 --> 00:06:59,712
I've got it!

119
00:07:00,212 --> 00:07:02,340
What's up?
What did you get?

120
00:07:05,092 --> 00:07:08,763
How to find out the name of
the guy who was following me today.

121
00:07:09,221 --> 00:07:10,473
How are you going to do it?

122
00:07:10,765 --> 00:07:12,725
I'm going to use the rules of
the Death Note to my advantage.

123
00:07:13,559 --> 00:07:14,644
If I write the cause of death...

124
00:07:14,810 --> 00:07:16,520
I have an additional
6 minutes and 4O seconds

125
00:07:16,646 --> 00:07:19,690
to record specific conditions
and time of death.

126
00:07:20,316 --> 00:07:24,904
I wonder how free I can
be with these conditions?

127
00:07:25,821 --> 00:07:27,198
I'm going to test it out.

128
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:30,201
THE FOLLOWING MORNING

129
00:07:33,037 --> 00:07:34,288
Yes, it's me.

130
00:07:35,831 --> 00:07:38,584
Another six inmates?

131
00:07:39,293 --> 00:07:40,461
All heart attacks?!

132
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,921
It's Kira.

133
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:43,631
What?

134
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:47,301
Three of them exhibited bizarre behavior
before they died?!

135
00:07:48,094 --> 00:07:49,303
What do you mean?!

136
00:07:49,470 --> 00:07:51,097
They didn't just die from
simple heart attacks?

137
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:55,518
Well, they died of heart attacks,
but before one of them died...

138
00:07:55,643 --> 00:07:59,522
he drew a strange symbol
on the wall with blood from his finger.

139
00:07:59,939 --> 00:08:03,150
Another left a letter that doesn't seem
like a will or anything meaningful.

140
00:08:04,026 --> 00:08:08,447
The third escaped just to go
to the employee bathroom.

141
00:08:14,954 --> 00:08:16,497
Watari, what is it?

142
00:08:16,622 --> 00:08:20,710
<i>More victims, but their circumstances
are unlike those we've had before.</i>

143
00:08:21,502 --> 00:08:23,129
Unlike those before?

144
00:08:23,629 --> 00:08:26,966
<i>I shall send you an image of
the picture and letter left at the scene.</i>

145
00:08:27,216 --> 00:08:28,175
If you could.

146
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:32,471
<i>A note describing a fear of Kira.</i>

147
00:08:33,806 --> 00:08:37,977
<i>This can be taken as
something a criminal might do, but...</i>

148
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:41,147
<i>Kira can control the time of death.</i>

149
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:44,859
<i>If he can control actions
right before death as well...</i>

150
00:08:44,984 --> 00:08:46,193
<i>that would mean that...</i>

151
00:08:47,945 --> 00:08:48,696
<i>Chief!</i>

152
00:08:50,322 --> 00:08:52,658
<i>Regarding these current victims.</i>

153
00:08:52,867 --> 00:08:54,535
<i>Don't let the media know anything</i>

154
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:57,163
<i>aside from the fact that
they died of heart attacks.</i>

155
00:08:57,872 --> 00:09:02,001
<i>It's possible that Kira
was performing some kind of test.</i>

156
00:09:02,126 --> 00:09:07,298
<i>If that's the case, we'd only
be giving him the results.</i>

157
00:09:07,882 --> 00:09:08,924
I see...

158
00:09:09,216 --> 00:09:10,676
I-| understand.

159
00:09:11,093 --> 00:09:13,429
Performing tests on criminals?

160
00:09:13,554 --> 00:09:14,722
That's horrible...

161
00:09:14,847 --> 00:09:18,100
He's playing with peoples' lives
as if this is a game.

162
00:09:18,225 --> 00:09:19,518
This is unforgivable!

163
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:24,648
<i>If Kira is using criminals
as test subjects...</i>

164
00:09:26,525 --> 00:09:28,152
<i>What is he trying to achieve?</i>

165
00:09:35,409 --> 00:09:37,078
Look at this, Ryuk.

166
00:09:37,453 --> 00:09:42,333
The results of yesterday's test have
already been input into Dad's computer.

167
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:44,585
KEITO NAWARAMI: KIDNAPPING MURDER

168
00:09:44,710 --> 00:09:46,629
KEITO NAWARAMI: KIDNAPPING MURDER

169
00:09:46,629 --> 00:09:46,670
The Death Note will work
for what I have in mind.

170
00:09:47,171 --> 00:09:48,631
What do you mean by that?

171
00:09:49,048 --> 00:09:50,508
One escaped...

172
00:09:50,633 --> 00:09:52,676
and went to the bathroom
I had designated in the Death Note.

173
00:09:53,219 --> 00:09:57,389
Another drew the same symbol
I had drawn in the Death Note.

174
00:09:57,389 --> 00:09:57,848
TAMIKl: HEART ATTACK, ESCAPES FROM CELL. DIES 6 P.M.
IVIASAAKI: HEART ATTACK, DRAVVS SYMBOL ON VVALL

175
00:09:57,848 --> 00:10:01,811
Yet another wrote the same letter
I had written in the Death Note.

176
00:10:03,062 --> 00:10:06,232
These three did exactly what I wanted.

177
00:10:07,274 --> 00:10:11,112
I purposely wrote very difficult tasks
for the other three.

178
00:10:12,113 --> 00:10:16,200
YUZO FURA: DIES IN FRONT OF THE
EIFFEL TOWER FRANCE, TODAY AT 6 P.M.

179
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:16,450
The first was to "Die in front of the
Eiffel Tower in an hour."

180
00:10:17,243 --> 00:10:22,540
It's physically impossible to go from
a prison in Japan to France in an hour.

181
00:10:22,998 --> 00:10:26,210
So this never happened and ended
as just a regular heart attack.

182
00:10:26,585 --> 00:10:32,007
The next was to "draw a picture of L's face
on the prison wall," but...

183
00:10:32,591 --> 00:10:34,844
One can't draw the faces...
of people they don't know.

184
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:36,387
I see.

185
00:10:36,846 --> 00:10:45,062
SHINSHIRO YAIVIAIVIAE: HEART ATTACK VVRITES A NOTE STATING "I KNOVV
THAT L IS SLJSPICIOLJS OF THE JAPANESE POLICE." DIES AT 6 P.M.

186
00:10:45,688 --> 00:10:49,441
I thought this one might work,
but it didn't happen.

187
00:10:49,525 --> 00:10:52,319
Which means that people can't write

188
00:10:52,444 --> 00:10:57,199
about things they don't know or things
they didn't come up with on their own.

189
00:10:57,908 --> 00:11:01,537
In short, it means that even
the Death Note can't do the impossible.

190
00:11:02,288 --> 00:11:06,417
But as long as it's something
the person is realisticallly likely to do,

191
00:11:06,625 --> 00:11:09,628
I can control them as much as
I want before he dies.

192
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:11,130
You've figured that out...

193
00:11:11,589 --> 00:11:14,675
But what are you trying to do, Light?

194
00:11:15,426 --> 00:11:19,263
I and the police will never
figure out my true goal.

195
00:11:19,763 --> 00:11:21,056
The great detective
is probably trying

196
00:11:21,182 --> 00:11:25,686
to decipher the picture and
the letter those criminals left.

197
00:11:26,437 --> 00:11:29,398
<i>They're absolutely meaningless
final words...</i>

198
00:11:31,775 --> 00:11:37,406
<i>If Kira used those criminals as guinea pigs,
he's about to start something.</i>

199
00:11:38,616 --> 00:11:41,744
<i>If he moves now,
there is the chance that...</i>

200
00:11:41,869 --> 00:11:44,496
<i>the FBI will notice someone
acting suspiciously.</i>

201
00:11:44,997 --> 00:11:49,210
<i>But if he has a different goal in mind...</i>

202
00:11:49,335 --> 00:11:52,880
<i>the letter and picture might
be some kind of message...</i>

203
00:11:54,089 --> 00:11:55,090
<i>Is this it?</i>

204
00:11:55,341 --> 00:11:58,177
I DO YOU KNOW

205
00:11:58,302 --> 00:11:59,887
Well... It's time for the main act.

206
00:12:00,429 --> 00:12:01,430
The "main act"?

207
00:12:01,847 --> 00:12:03,307
Yesterday on the news...

208
00:12:03,724 --> 00:12:05,476
There was a drug addict who tried
to rob a bank,

209
00:12:05,601 --> 00:12:08,687
WANTED CRIMINAL
KIICHIRO OSOREDA

210
00:12:08,687 --> 00:12:08,979
He attacked civilians and escaped.

211
00:12:09,188 --> 00:12:10,147
I'll use him.

212
00:12:11,273 --> 00:12:12,942
It's last minute, but I'm sure
I can find someone...

213
00:12:13,776 --> 00:12:15,069
I'll try to ask out a few.

214
00:12:15,527 --> 00:12:17,363
Ask out... "a few"?

215
00:12:17,821 --> 00:12:22,326
Yeah... Ryuk, I may not look it,
but I'm pretty popular.

216
00:12:31,835 --> 00:12:36,632
Hello? Huh, Light?
Good morning...

217
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:00,155
<i>He's still following me, isn't he?</i>

218
00:13:00,823 --> 00:13:01,782
<i>That's perfect.</i>

219
00:13:02,283 --> 00:13:03,659
<i>If my shadow wasn't here,</i>

220
00:13:03,701 --> 00:13:06,161
<i>there would be no point in what
I'm going to do next.</i>

221
00:13:11,709 --> 00:13:13,460
Light!

222
00:13:13,794 --> 00:13:15,462
- A date?
- Yeah.

223
00:13:16,338 --> 00:13:18,340
It's a date,
no matter how you look at it.

224
00:13:19,008 --> 00:13:21,343
Even to my shadow...

225
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:23,345
It's not a normal date, is it?

226
00:13:23,846 --> 00:13:27,057
You said you found a way
to find out your shadow's name, but...

227
00:13:27,975 --> 00:13:30,019
What do you plan to do?

228
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:35,149
Huh? Ryuk, didn't you see
what I wrote in the Death Note?

229
00:13:35,232 --> 00:13:38,402
Nah. It would be boring to peek.

230
00:13:38,736 --> 00:13:41,071
Then just be patient and
watch what happens.

231
00:13:43,365 --> 00:13:45,701
Sorry, did I keep you waiting?

232
00:13:45,868 --> 00:13:47,369
No, not at all!

233
00:13:47,703 --> 00:13:50,581
Anyway, I haven't been to
Space Land since junior high!

234
00:13:50,998 --> 00:13:54,710
I'm so excited!
And I get to be alone with you!

235
00:13:55,044 --> 00:13:56,045
Y-Yeah.

236
00:13:58,047 --> 00:14:01,717
<i>On weekdays, he only goes
to school and his prep courses.</i>

237
00:14:02,551 --> 00:14:06,096
<i>An occasional date on his days off.
He's a normal...</i>

238
